INSERT INTO `TestResult` VALUES (1,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Scripts should be included at the bottom of the page, not in the head','It may be better to add the HTML5 shim separately from Modernizr, load Modernizr at the bottom of the page, and see if FOUT is a problem. \r\n\r\nAlso, you might ask yourself if Modernizr is necessary for your site. Modernizr is an excellent way to polyfill HTML5, but if you\'re not really using it you might not want it to block your content.',25),(2,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Body copy is difficult to read at current font size','Suggestion: increase the body copy font size or consider using a font that is more legible at smaller point sizes.',50),(3,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Links cannot be accurately selected in mobile view','We suggest using media queries to make links larger and wider-spaced for mobile. The fingertap guideline is 44px.',40),(4,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'IE version of web font not included','To support web fonts in Internet Explorer all you need to do is 1) include an .eot font and 2) add an additional CSS declaration. Here\'s [Paul Irish\'s bulletproof syntax](http://paulirish.com/2009/bulletproof-font-face-implementation-syntax/).',55),(5,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'17% of stylesheet /css/dedb495.css is not used for %url%','Suggestion: remove unused styles.',50),(6,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Missing img alt attribute','Missing the alt attribute in an image may seem like a small thing, but it is very important for accessibility, and it is required.',16),(7,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Metadata content is empty','`<meta name=\"author\" content=\"\">`\r\n\r\n`<meta name=\"description\" content=\"\">`',15),(8,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'\"Story-tellers\" misspelled with em dash','This is a minor issue. However, the word story-teller will not be properly indexed by search engines. We recommend using CSS to achieve the desired look.',18),(9,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Logo does not have a consistent appearance across browsers','The site logo is made with a web font. It\'s an advanced idea, and I commend you for it. However, you will not be able to control the way the logo looks across web browsers. For branding reasons, you may want to make the logo a graphic.',30),(10,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'HTTP requests unnecessary','Since %url% is a single-page web site, the benefit of external CSS and scripts is lost. The HTTP requests may not be worth the performance hit in this case.',15),(11,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Single quotes, double quotes, and no quotes are used for attribute values','Suggestion: be consistent and use double quotes.',7),(12,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'HTML5 element does not need XHTML close tag','`<img src=\"img/madefire-m.png\" width=67 height=50 />`\r\n\r\ncan be \r\n\r\n`<img src=\"img/madefire-m.png\" width=67 height=50>`',7),(59,3,'HTML','FaviconMissing',NULL,'No favicon included','Favicons are 16 x 16 pixel images that appear in browsers next to location bars, bookmarks and tabs. They improve the user experience, they are easy to make, and they are cute.',30),(118,5,'Script','ScriptsInHead',NULL,'Scripts should be included at the bottom of the page, not in the head','There is a habit of putting script links in the head of HTML documents. Scripts usually do not need to be loaded first and they block content rendering.\r\n\r\nScripts block in a special way, unlike stylesheets, and no more than two can be download and parsed at once. You have 2 scripts linked in the head. \r\n\r\nWe suggest putting scripts at the bottom of the page, before the close body tag. For Internet Explorer only, you can also add defer=defer to the script tag.',70),(119,5,'HTML','AmpersandUnescapedInLink',NULL,'Ampersands (&) in links need to be converted to \"&amp;\" when written in HTML','When we write links in the body of our HTML document we need to convert \"&\" to \"&amp;\". (It is not necessary to do this otherwise: for example, when pasting into emails or browser location bars.) As attribute values for \"src\" and \"href\", plain ampersands are invalid. An unescaped ampersand was found here:\r\n\r\n`http://www.google.com/url?sa=t&rct=j&q=whine-o-meter&source=web&cd=2 &ved=0CCIQFjAB&url=http%3A%2F%2Fitunes.apple.com%2Fus%2Fapp%2Fwhine -o-meter%2Fid348828301%3Fmt%3D8&ei=kNimTorXJMWwiQLG1pzODQ&usg=AFQjC NGXE2GptBmXYc6QCL4UFraGQkbPXg&cad=rja`\r\n\r\nBrowsers usually interpret links with unescaped ampersands just fine. However, it\'s a bad practice and there are pitfalls. For example, if you wrote a query string like \"?copy1=test&copy2=test\" a browser might interpret this as \"?copy1=test©2.\"',20),(120,5,'HTML','FaviconMissing',NULL,'No favicon included','Favicons are 16x16 pixel images that appear in browsers next to location bars, bookmarks and tabs. They improve the user experience and they are easy to make. To create a favicon you can use an [online tool](http://www.favicon.cc/) or install a [Photoshop plugin](http://www.telegraphics.com.au/sw/). Name the file favicon.ico, put it in your root web directory, and add the following to your html head:\r\n\r\n`<link rel=\"icon\" type=\"image/x-icon\" href=\"/favicon.ico\" />`',30),(121,5,'HTML','HasDocumentWrite',NULL,'document.write() should not be used',NULL,9),(122,4,'HTML','GifsUsed',NULL,'GIF images should be replaced with PNGs','%url% has 5 gifs with a total file size of 51.98KB.\r\n\r\nPNG images compress better and there are patent issues around using GIFs. We suggest PNG-8 for non-transparent images, PNG-24 for transparent images, and JPEG for photos.',10),(123,4,'Script','ScriptsInHead',NULL,'Scripts should be included at the bottom of the page, not in the head','There is a habit of putting script links in the head of HTML documents. Scripts usually do not need to be loaded first and they block content rendering.\r\n\r\nScripts block in a special way, unlike stylesheets, and no more than two can be download and parsed at once. You have 6 scripts linked in the head. \r\n\r\nWe suggest putting scripts at the bottom of the page, before the close body tag. For Internet Explorer only, you can also add defer=defer to the script tag.',70),(124,4,'HTML','ManyImagesFlag',NULL,'A questionably large number of images (15) used','Images are HTTP requests that slow down rendering and should be minimized. \r\n\r\nUnless your HTML document is something as primitive as an HTML email, images should not be used for layout. Replace corners, spacers, shadows, gradients...etc. with CSS.',8),(125,4,'HTML','JavascriptInHref',NULL,'The JavaScript pseudo-protocol should not be used at the target of a link','Found the JavaScript pseudo-protocol \"javascript:\" on the following lines:\r\n\r\n`<a href=\"javascript:launchRemote(\'https://www.prosper.com/security/thaw te_verified.aspx\',\'thawte_popup\',\'370\',\'800\')\"> <img src=\"/Images/p artners/thawte/ssl_valid_english_vB1.gif\"></a>`  \n\r\r\n\r\nSimply put, links should be links, not javascript. It\'s more appropriate to use the onClick event handler and to apply JavaScript to the click of an element. Better code would be:\r\n\r\n`<a href=\"/current_page.html\" onClick=\"doOnClick()\">`\r\n\r\nHowever, there is no reason for this element to be a link, especially since it behaves more like a button. I would use `<span>`, `<div>` or `<button>`, and apply a style that sets the cursor to pointer for that element, so that the user gets the visual cue that the element is clickable. \r\n\r\n`<div onClick=\"doOnClick()\" class=\"fauxButton\">`\r\n\r\nWe can improve on this a bit more, but the important short-term goal is replace \"javascript:\" in links.',20),(126,4,'HTML','ImgAltAttributeMissing',NULL,'Missing img alt attribute','Missing the alt attribute in an image may seem like a small thing, but it is important for accessibility as well as required. You should add alt text to the following:\r\n\r\n`<img src=\"http://www.prosper.com/prm/images/blue2011/invest-returns-chart 120118.png\">`  \n\r`<img src=\"/Images/pages/home/homepage/individual_loans_animation_draft_v1 .gif\">`  \n\r`<img src=\"/Images/pages/home/homepage/promo-icon-quote.png\">`  \n\r`<img src=\"/Images/pages/home/homepage/promo-icon-earn-100.png\">`  \n\r`<img src=\"/Images/pages/home/homepage/featured-in.png\">`  \n\r`<img src=\"/Images/partners/thawte/ssl_valid_english_vB1.gif\">`  \n\r`<img src=\"/images/partners/truste/finalmark.gif\">`  \n\r',25),(127,4,'HTML','MissingImgHeightOrWidth',NULL,'Images should have height and width set','Height and width are not officially required attributes for `<img>`. However, including those attributes guarantees faster content download. That information also helps the browser determine the viewport space for the image, making rendering smoother. We recommend adding the correct pixel dimensions to the following images found at %url%:\r\n\r\n`<img src=\"/prm/images/promo/promo_prospective_investors_anim_2012-4-13.gi f\" alt=\"More Reasons to Invest\">`  \n\r`<img src=\"http://www.prosper.com/prm/images/blue2011/invest-returns-chart 120118.png\">`  \n\r`<img src=\"/Images/pages/home/homepage/individual_loans_animation_draft_v1 .gif\">`  \n\r`<img src=\"/Images/pages/home/homepage/promo-icon-quote.png\">`  \n\r`<img src=\"/Images/pages/home/homepage/promo-icon-earn-100.png\">`  \n\r`<img src=\"/Images/pages/home/homepage/featured-in.png\">`  \n\r`<img src=\"/Images/partners/thawte/ssl_valid_english_vB1.gif\">`  \n\r`<img src=\"/images/partners/truste/finalmark.gif\">`  \n\r',30),(128,4,'HTML5','ClassNameSameAsHtml5Element',NULL,'An element has a class name that is also the name of an HTML5 or HTML tag. This indicates that the element can be replaced with a more semantic tag','`(530) <div id=\"M_divFooter\" class=\"footer\">\r`  \n\r`(62) <div class=\"header\">\r`  \n\r',20),(129,4,'HTML','ManyInlineStylesFlag',NULL,'10 inline styles detected','While you may have a good reason to write styles inline using the \"style\" attribute, generally it is not a good practice. It makes bloated code, styles are not re-usable, styling has too much specificity...etc. We only make this suggestion when the sum of inline styles has reached a suspicious threshold (>8), and we suggest identifying common styles and them in a style sheet. When you need to update or change your styles, you will thank us.',20),(130,4,'HTML','HasDocumentWrite',NULL,'document.write() should not be used',NULL,9),(131,4,'HTML','DeprecatedAttributeOptimized',NULL,'\"align\" is a deprecated HTML4 attribute in div','`<div align=\"center\">`\r\n\r\nWe suggest you use an HTML validator to discover and replace deprecated attributes. \r\n\r\n[W3C Markup Validation Service](http://validator.w3.org/)\r\n[Validator.nu (X)HTML5 Validator](http://html5.validator.nu/)',9),(132,4,'HTML','LargeScriptNotMinified',NULL,'Minify scripts to improve web site performance','The following 45.21KB script could have whitespace removed.\r\n\r\n`(21) <script src=\"/script/javascript.js?v=201204021715\" type=\"text/javascript\"></script>`  \n\r',33),(133,4,'HTML','LargeScriptNotMinified',NULL,'Minify scripts to improve web site performance','The following 45.21KB script could have whitespace removed:\r\n\r\n`(21) <script src=\"/script/javascript.js?v=201204021715\" type=\"text/javascript\"></script>`  \n\r',33),(134,4,'HTML','LargeStylesheetNotMinified',NULL,'Minify CSS to improve web site performance','The following 119.19KB style sheet could have whitespace removed: `<link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"/static/css/style.css?v=201204021715\">`  \n\r',33),(150,6,'HTML5','NotHtml5Doctype',NULL,'Site should be updated to HTML5, the evolving new standard','If this is a site under development, versus a retired page of content, you probably want to make it HTML5 instead of XHTML 1.0 Transitional. This transition should be as easy as changing the doctype to `<!doctype html>`. \r\n\r\nIf you wish, you may also make the character encoding meta tag shorter. What had looked something like this:\r\n\r\n`<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html;charset=utf-8\" />`\r\n\r\nCan be replaced with this:\r\n\r\n`<meta charset=\"utf-8\">`\r\n\r\nAfter you make this change you\'ll want to run [HTML5 validation](http://html5.validator.nu/) against it. Here is a [direct link](http://html5.validator.nu/?doc=%url%) for running HTML5 validation against your site once you change the doctype.',99),(151,6,'HTML','GifsUsed',NULL,'GIF images should be replaced with PNGs','%url% has 4 gifs with a total file size of 14.49KB.\r\n\r\nPNG images compress better and there are patent issues around using GIFs. We suggest PNG-8 for non-transparent images, PNG-24 for transparent images, and JPEG for photos.',10),(152,6,'HTML','ImgAltAttributeMissing',NULL,'Missing img alt attribute','Missing the alt attribute in an image may seem like a small thing, but it is important for accessibility as well as required. You should add alt text to the following:\r\n\r\n`<img src=\"/pix/eoai.gif\" alt=\"\" id=\"eoai\">`  \n\r',25),(153,6,'HTML','BoldTags',NULL,'Bold tags do not have much semantic meaning. Replace them with heading level or strong tags','This is a very minor issue. However, if you enclosed text with `<b>` because it is important text, it would be better to use `<strong>`; `<strong>` means important whereas `<b>` means \"visually disctinct from text that surrounds it.\"\r\n\r\nIf the text in question can be considered a headline, it\'s best to use a heading level tag: `<h1> ... <h6>`.\r\n\r\n`(57) <b>15, 2002</b>`  \n\r`(468) <b>1534-0295</b>`  \n\r',9),(154,6,'HTML','HasDocumentWrite',NULL,'document.write() should not be used',NULL,9),(155,6,'HTML','DeprecatedAttributeOptimized',NULL,'\"border\" is a deprecated HTML4 attribute for <img>','`<img src=\"/d/betterliving/ie6.gif\" width=\"404\" height=\"104\" border=\"0\" alt=\"IE6 mangles menu bar.\" title=\"IE6 mangles menu bar.\" />`\r\n\r\nWe suggest you use an HTML validator to discover and replace deprecated attributes. Here are a couple options:\r\n\r\n[W3C Markup Validation Service](http://validator.w3.org/)\r\n\r\n[Validator.nu (X)HTML5 Validator](http://html5.validator.nu/)',9),(174,7,'HTML','ImgAltAttributeMissing',NULL,'Missing img alt attribute','Missing the alt attribute in an image may seem like a small thing, but it is important for accessibility as well as required. You should add alt text to the following:\r\n\r\n`(1) <img src=\"img/madefire-m.png\" width=\"67\" height=\"50\">`  \n\r',25),(175,7,'HTML','AmpersandUnescapedInLink',NULL,'Ampersands (&) in links need to be converted to \"&amp;\" when written in HTML','When we write links in the body of our HTML document we need to convert \"&\" to \"&amp;\". (It is not necessary to do this otherwise: for example, when pasting into emails or browser location bars.) As attribute values for \"src\" and \"href\", plain ampersands are invalid. An unescaped ampersand was found here:\r\n\r\n`mailto:contact@madefire.com?subject=Newsletter%20Signup&body=Plea se%20sign%20me%20up%20for%20the%20Madefire%20newsletter. `\r\n\r\nBrowsers usually interpret links with unescaped ampersands just fine. However, it\'s a bad practice and there are pitfalls. For example, if you wrote a query string like \"?copy1=test&copy2=test\" a browser might interpret this as \"?copy1=test©2.\"',20),(176,7,'HTML','MetadataContentEmpty',NULL,'Metadata content is empty','If the content is empty, you might as well remove the meta tag.\r\n\r\n`(1) <meta name=\"description\" content=\"\">`  \n\r`(1) <meta name=\"author\" content=\"\">`  \n\r',10),(177,7,'HTML','FaviconMissing',NULL,'No favicon included','Favicons are 16x16 pixel images that appear in browsers next to location bars, bookmarks and tabs. They improve the user experience and they are easy to make. To create a favicon you can use an [online tool](http://www.favicon.cc/) or install a [Photoshop plugin](http://www.telegraphics.com.au/sw/). Name the file favicon.ico, put it in your root web directory, and add the following to the `<head>` element of your HTML:\r\n\r\n`<link rel=\"icon\" type=\"image/x-icon\" href=\"/favicon.ico\">`',30),(178,7,'HTML','DeprecatedAttributeOptimized',NULL,'\"width\" is a deprecated HTML4 attribute for <!doctype>','`<!doctype html> <!--[if lt IE 7]><html class=\"no-js lt-ie9 lt-ie8 lt-ie7\" lang=en><![endif]--> <!--[if IE 7]><html class=\"no-js lt-ie9 lt-ie8\" lang=en><![endif]--> <!--[if IE 8]><html class=\"no-js lt-ie9\" lang=en><![endif]--> <!--[if gt IE 8]><!--> <html class=\"no-js lt-ie9\" lang=en> <!--<![endif]--> <head> <meta charset=utf-8> <title>Madefire</title> <meta name=description content=\"\"> <meta name=author content=\"\"> <meta name=viewport content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"> <link rel=stylesheet href=\'css/dedb495.css\'> <script src=\"js/libs/modernizr-2.0.6.min.js\"></script> </head> <body> <header> <div class=col1> <ul> <li><a href=\"mailto:contact@madefire.com?subject=Newsletter%20Signup&body=Please%20sign%20me%20up%20for%20the%20Madefire%20newsletter.\">Newsletter</a></li> <li><a href=\"mailto:contact@madefire.com\">Contact</a></li> </ul> </div> <div class=col2> <img src=\"img/madefire-m.png\" width=67 height=50 /> Madefire </div> <div class=col3> <span class=quote>&#8220;This tool will empower the next wave of storytelling.&#8221;</span> <span class=attribution>Toni Schneider CEO Automattic</span> </div> </header> <div id=main role=main> <div id=hero> <div id=hiring> <a href=\"http://madefire.jobscore.com/\" target=_blank>We\'re Hiring</a> </div> <h1>Calling all story&#8212;tellers</h1> </div> <div id=story> <div class=col1> <p><strong>Madefire:</strong> Long ago we drew down fire from the heavens, lit up our caves with life-giving flames, and set about documenting the story of Us on those rough-hewn walls in ochre daubs.</p> <p>Here is where \'the story\' in picture form began, here is where we first captured the startling imagery our imaginations afforded us, birthing worlds and realms peopled by beings that did not exist.</p> <p>The story grew.</p> <p>Through the ages of man we raised physical and literary temples in the name of our ever-evolving imaginative prowess. We lived, and live still, surrounded by and within our dreamings.</p> </div> <div class=col2> <p>Man made fire, and from it grew \'the story\'.</p> <p>We\'re in an amazing age right now. There have, over the centuries, been times when \'the story\' evolved&#8212;took a seismic leap forward. Those cave paintings were one such leap, this digital age beckons another. Storytelling can evolve again in ways limited only by our&nbsp;imaginations.</p> <p>At <strong>Madefire</strong> we\'ve been working towards an experience at once universal and personal, private and shared. The interconnectivity of everyone rewrites what has gone before. Stories no longer need to happen in linear space but can explode into clouds. Readers need not dwell in the modern day analog of that ancient cave&#8212;but can instead share their tales with a global tribe.</p> </div> <div class=col3> <p>The advent of the tablet computer has changed storytelling by adding further dimension to the potency of words and&nbsp;pictures.</p> <p>With A-list story talent, minds culled from leading technological innovators, and experience that combines leadership in all forms of media, we\'re confident that we\'re cultivating an experience people will want to share, and share in. We\'re working with the best, and that includes you&#8212;you that come with us and partake in an evolutionary journey that genuinely could change the way we experience \'the story\' forever.</p> <p>&#8212;MF</p> </div> </div> </div> <footer> </footer> <script>var _gaq=[[\"_setAccount\",\"UA-28954524-1\"],[\"_trackPageview\"]];(function(e,a){var c=e.createElement(a),b=e.getElementsByTagName(a)[0];c.src=(\"https:\"==location.protocol?\"//ssl\":\"//www\")+\".google-analytics.com/ga.js\";b.parentNode.insertBefore(c,b)}(document,\"script\"));</script> </body> </html>`\r\n\r\nWe suggest you use an HTML validator to discover and replace deprecated attributes. Here are a couple options:\r\n\r\n[W3